CHAT.comment: Teaching. Mother and Child sit on floor. First Mother teaches Child to string beads. Then Mother teaches Child to sort black and white buttons into two boxes. Child is quite intelligible.

u.a: points to other side of bead .
watches; then attempts to do her bead .
reaches for different bead in box .
takes round bead out of box and holds up for Child .
pushes string through bead Mother is holding .
pushes on short end sticking through bead .
starts to pull string back out .
takes short end sticking out of bead .
pushes short end back toward bead .

g.ga: or hold this in your hand

u.a: tries to take bead that's already on string .
starts to push string through bead .
pushes string through to other side .
